The following code (in `CustomHierarchy()`) is only called once (once the custom heirarchy is initialized): 

        if (onoff == true)
        {
            EditorApplication.hierarchyWindowItemOnGUI += HandleHierarchyWindowItemOnGUI;
        }

Essentially `EditorApplication.hierarchyWindowItemOnGUI` is an event handler and when you add the function you are effectively telling the application to run `HandleHierarchyWindowItemOnGUI()` everytime the event is triggered. **You only do this once**, therefore trying to check if `onoff` is true will not do anything because the function (`HandleHierarchyWindowItemOnGUI()`) has already been attached to the event handler.

Instead put the `if (onoff)` statement in the actual `HandleHierarchyWindowItemOnGUI()` function:

    private static void HandleHierarchyWindowItemOnGUI(int instanceID, Rect selectionRect)
    {
		if(onoff){
			... //Do the stuff you had in this function
		}
	}

Therefore, it won&#39;t actually use the code you want executed.

